This article is a presidential proclamation issued by Barack Obama on March 1, 2013, to commemorate the 10th anniversary of the United States Department of Homeland Security (DHS). The proclamation highlights the DHS's role in keeping the American people safe since its establishment in the aftermath of the September 11 attacks. It acknowledges the department's efforts in securing borders, ports, critical infrastructure, and cyber networks, as well as its work in addressing immigration issues and improving preparedness for national emergencies and natural disasters. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to recognize the DHS for its contributions in improving America's readiness and resilience.